  <description><![CDATA[<p>Imagine being just step's from the clear blue sea and white sandy shores, and feeling the warm Sardinian sun on your face - this could be your reality. The Hotel Stella Maris is near the small seafront village of Villasimius in the <a data-udi="umb://document/cc3361d2d7a945d38852da5e20516d75" href="/{localLink:umb://document/cc3361d2d7a945d38852da5e20516d75}" title="Southern Sardinia">south of Sardinia</a>. With its own private beach on the bay of Campolongu and plenty of sun loungers free for you to use throughout your stay, it feels like a little spot of paradise. Lush gardens of palms, oleander and juniper trees are the only thing separating the hotel from the coast. A cobbled path leads back towards the terraced pool where you'll find even more areas made purely for relaxation - we love chilling with a good book on one of the gazebo beds dotted about the place. </p>
<p>The hotel itself has a lot of character and inside the décor is vibrant and inviting and the rooms are the same. They're nice and spacious and if you go for a classic sea view room you'll have a furnished balcony too. The staff are really friendly and will go out of their way to help you with anything you need. We can't forget to mention the food - it's delicious so save some room. There's such a good choice each evening including some of the best fresh seafood dishes we've tasted. </p>
<p>Car hire is recommended for this hotel. Hotel Stella Maris is approx. 1 hour 15 minutes from Cagliari airport</p>]]></description>
